channel.title: Static IP HELP!
channel.description: I followed Davidi2's Tutorial and OMG! This Screwed Up my internet really bad i am using windows seven. I went To network and internet connections change adapter settings right click on my connection than i had 2 things that i can click properties on.There Is Internet Protocol Version 6 (TCP/IP) and Internet Protocol Version 4 (TCP/IP). I tend to click on the one that is more Similar to the picture above. So I click on IPV 4 (TCP/IP). I Put Down all my settings. MY INTERNET SCREWED UP! Turns out it deleted my network.So i got it fixed =D. But the next day i got my mom pissed so she took the internet ! And when she came back i connected the Internet and HOLY! It changed from 65.95.113.198 - 65.92.122.90. Also my CMD IPCONFIG ALL Changed! My default gateway is like 0.0.0.0 WTF! HELP!

item.title: Static IP HELP!
item.dc:creator: @WiseMen WiseMen
item.description:
@WiseMen wrote:

You’ve got a modem, that’s why. She unplugged your modem cable. You’ve got to leave your modem off for like 4-12 hours, and it’ll change. Happen to me when I had a modem but now I have a Dynamic IP (Router)
